Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 30-A MRSA §2532, as amended by PL 2019, c. 288, §2, is further amended
3 to read:
4 §2532. Referendum recount procedure
5 In the case of a referendum, a recount must be granted upon written application of 10%
6 or 100, whichever is less, of the registered voters in the municipality, except that,
7 notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, if a municipal referendum passes or
8 fails by less than 1% of all the votes cast in the referendum, including any blank ballots
9 cast, an automatic recount is required. The application must designate a person to be the
10 official representative of the registered voters requesting the recount including the person's
11 legal name, mailing address, residence address and telephone number. An official
12 representative for the registered voters opposing the recount may be established by
13 submission of an affidavit signed by 10 registered voters of the municipality. The time
14 limits, rules and all other matters applying to candidates under section 2531‑B apply
15 equally to a referendum recount, except that provisions in section 2531‑B applicable to the
16 candidate requesting the recount and candidates not requesting the recount apply, for
17 purposes of this section, to the official representative of the referendum recount and the
18 official representative, if any, of the voters opposed to the recount, respectively.
19 SUMMARY
2200 This bill requires that, if a municipal referendum passes or fails by less than 1% of all
2211 the votes cast in the referendum, including any blank ballots cast, an automatic recount is
2222 required.
